)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   <br><br>BTW - who fugged up this thread? the left table is wider than normal <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br><br><br><br><br>Added: <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> UPLOADING</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - Feb. 15, 2002<br><br>Well, Images... you or someone has just made a spiffy new image (saved .jpg or .gif, not larger than 50kb in size)<br><br>Here's how you get it on the net so you can add it to your sig (using <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.geocities.com/ezboardsigtut/htmltut.html#images">this tag</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->) - I'll try to keep it simple<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 1)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> You need a server... basically, some place on the net that will let you upload your image, so that others can access that web page to view the picture (<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.netfirms.com/">www.netfirms.com/</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> (thx to Karm Hundredfists) or <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.freewebspace.com/">www.freewebspace.com/</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->... or there are many others, just do a search on <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.google.com">www.google.com</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> if you dont like those... or your isp usually gives you some space to work with)<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 2)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> You need an uploading program (ftp)... (really depends on your web server though, some dont allow 3rd person ftp) like <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.cuteftp.com">www.cuteftp.com</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> or <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.wsftp.com">www.wsftp.com</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 3)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> After you have those, and you find out how to connect to your server using the new ftp program you have (they will normally tell you what the ftp address is to put int the connection area... ftp.attbi.com, or ftp.freewebspace.com or whatever it is)... you must find the image on your HD, and transfer it to the server... usually by double clicking it<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> 4)</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Once you have the image on the server, you can now link to it and people will see it in your signature...<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Things to note:</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> You can <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> NOT</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> link to images on your HD, unless it is set up as a server (which it probably isnt)<br>This <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> will</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> take effort on your part... I wish I could explain everything simply and easily enough that everyone could understand it... but it can be difficult at times... use the <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>H</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->elp menu on things... they will explain how to do stuff (usually)<br><br>There you go... I will add this to the above website later...<br><br><br><br><br><br><br><br>You get to learn how to make a signature for your EZboard avatar today...<br><br>First off, we need to go to the area where you will write your sig<br><br><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://ezboardpics.homestead.com/files/ContCent.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br><br><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://ezboardpics.homestead.com/files/EditPrefsmall.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br><br>Scroll down till you see this area:<br><br><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://ezboardpics.homestead.com/files/SigBox.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br><br>Ok... now you need to put the proper HTML in that box, so that a signature will show up when you post... heres the basic stuff:<br><br>----------------------------------------------<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    Text</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->:  To put text in HTML, just type it like you would regular text, no tags or anything needed.<br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>    Example</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->:<br><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>HTML in sig box</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->:  This is text... no knowledge of HTML is really needed for it<br><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>What apears in sig</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->:  This is text... no knowledge of HTML is really needed for it<br><br>----------------------------------------------<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    Line Break</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->:  HTML will not naturally make a break in a line of text..., unless you put &lt;BR&gt; when you want one<br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>    Example</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->:<br><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>HTML in sig box</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->:  This is a line &lt;BR&gt; after it has been broken.<br><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>What apears in sig</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->:  <br><br>This is a line<br>after it has been broken<br><br>----------------------------------------------<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    Links</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->:  Links are called anchors in HTML... they use this basic tag -  <a href=url to be linked to>Text to be anchored</a><br>Quotes can be included around the url (e.g. - &quot;http://www.servername.com") if it helps you read them better, but they are not needed.<br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    Note</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->:  There are a few extra things you can put into anchored links to... the one most often used is probably the target=_blank command... it makes the link open up in a new window, instead of showing it in the window your already in (e.g. - <a href=http://www.monkly-business.com target=_blank>MB</a> - <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    There MUST</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> be a space between the url and the target command)<br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>    Example</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->:<br><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>HTML in sig box</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->:  <a href=http://www.monkly-business.com>Monkly-Business</a><br><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>What apears in sig</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->: <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.monkly-business.com">Monkly-Business</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br><br>----------------------------------------------<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    Images</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->:  The basic HTML tag for an image is: &lt;img src=url of image&gt;<br>This will embed the image into the web page, for everyone to see...<br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>    Example</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->:<br><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>HTML in sig box</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->:  &lt;img src=http://images.slashdot.org/title.gif><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>What apears in sig</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END-->:  <!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://images.slashdot.org/title.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br><br>----------------------------------------------<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    Tables</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: Oh god, why did I mention this...<br>Anyway, the basic HTML for a table is as follows:<br>&lt;table width=# height=# border=#&gt; - Start of table<br>&lt;tr&gt; - Starts a horizontal ROW<br>&lt;td&gt; - Starts a vertical COLUMN<br>HTML CAN GO HERE<br>&lt;/td&gt; - ends the column<br>&lt;/tr&gt; - ends the row<br>&lt;/table&gt; - ends the table<br><br>Ok... I can't do an example of this on EZboard, as they do not have a [table] command, and HTML can not be used on this board... but I'll try to explain as best as I can:<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    height and width</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> denote the... you got it... height and width of the table (e.g. - width=640 height=480, would get you a table with dimensions 640x480) - <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i>    NOTE</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->:  If you do not assign a value to width and height or dont include them in your table tag at all, then the table will automatically size itself to what you are doing... which can be very helpful if you do not know what you are doing<br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    border</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> denotes the size of the border around the table (default set to 1... 0 makes no border)<br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    &lt;TR&gt; and &lt;TD&gt;</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> - You can have as many of these as you want, and any amount of HTML in each...<br><br><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://htmlgoodies.com/tutors/tbl.html">Click here if you did not understand and wish to learn more about how tables work...</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br><br>----------------------------------------------<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    Font</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->:  The &lt;font&gt;&lt;/font&gt; tag is a very powerful tag... with many options that can be used... here we go:<br>&lt;font size=#&gt; - Resizes the text between the &lt;font&gt; and &lt;/font&gt; tag<br><br>&lt;font color=%&gt; - % can be a few things... it can be the name of a basic color (e.g. - red, blue, yellow, pruple, etc.) or it can be the computer assigned value of a shade of a color: #XXXXXX (a pound sign, followed by a 6 digit code, in hex) - <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://primeshop.com/html/216colrs.htm">All the 6 numbered codes for every color you could ever want</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br><br>&lt;font face=name of font&gt; - This can be used to change your text to a different font (e.g. - New Time Roman or Gothic)... <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    NOTE</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->: Use a font that MOST computers should have... as it wont show up if you use a font that no one has ever heard of...<br><br>You can combine all of these into one font statement: &lt;font face=font size=# color=%&gt;Text to be fonted&lt;/font&gt;<br><br>----------------------------------------------<br><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    Tutorials</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->:  If you wish to learn more about HTML and how it works... please follow this link: <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.google.com/search?hl=en&amp;q=%22HTML+Tutorials%22">www.google.com/search?hl=en&amp;q=%22HTML+Tutorials%22</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> - Thank you<br><br>----------------------------------------------<br><br><br>Now that we've got some basic HTML in your sig box (click 'Save Preferences' button at bottom of page)... we can test it!  Go to a forum, I suggest Out of Character or General... but any can be used really, as you wont acutally be posting your sig anywhere... will you?<br><br>Next, click the 'Add topic' button at the top right or bottom right of the forum<br><br>do something similar to this:<br><br><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://ezboardpics.homestead.com/files/previewsmall.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br><br>as the picture illustrates... <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b>    USE THE PREVIEW BUTTON TO TEST YOUR SIGNATURE</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->!<br><br>Click the 'Add Post' button... you should get something like this (depending on what is in your Signature Box):<br><br><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://ezboardpics.homestead.com/files/lookat.jpg"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br><br>If it does not look right, open a new browser window, and go back to the beginning... and, after making the changes in your sig box area (and clicking save preferences), hit the back button on the 'Sig Test' post, and then click the 'Add Post' button again... Rinse, Repeat until done<br><br>I hope this helps some of you... and I'm sure i will work on it more as time goes by, so... i dub this 'How to make a sig.  v1.0b' <p>[46 Monk] <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=768"target=_blank>Meogi San</a> (Iksar) -- Vazaelle<BR>[54 Heretic] Revanant (Unknown) -- Brell</p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/umrmeogi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mr Meogi</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://home.attbi.com/~tiberium33/logos.gif" BORDER=0> at: 2/15/02 4:06:25